          <details>
            <summary>How are player rankings calculated?</summary>
            <p>Rankings are calculated from a player's top five performances at sanctioned offline tournaments, factoring placing, event value, and recency.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How do these rankings differ from a game's built-in online ladder or ranked mode?</summary>
            <p>Our rankings and in-game ladders measure different things. We evaluate performance in high-stakes <strong>offline tournaments</strong>, while ranked ladders reflect <strong>online consistency</strong> over many matches. Together they offer a fuller picture of competitive level.</p>
          </details>
          <details id="faq-online-events">
            <summary>Why aren’t online tournaments included?</summary>
            <p>We evaluate in-person events only, as online results can be affected by connectivity and environment differences.</p>
          </details>
          <details id="faq-fewer-events">
            <summary>Can a player’s ranking change if they attend fewer events?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Because the system emphasizes recent and top performances, players who compete less frequently can still improve their ranking by performing well at higher-value tournaments.</p>
          </details>
          <details id="faq-updates">
            <summary>How often are rankings updated?</summary>
            <p>Rankings are updated soon after the completion of major offline events to reflect the latest results.</p>
          </details>
